Looking to the south, on the left parapet of the porch, is a lone lantern, long since abandoned and even longer
it has remained without fuel. You wonder where you could find fuel for such an old looking lantern.
[-]
A lantern sits at rest on the ground. Or is it in motion? I never could tell.
[-]
You attach the lantern to your satchel. The extra weight is barely noticeable.
[-]
A lantern hangs from your satchel, unfortunately unlit.
